                  <summary>Agreement of sale, which is supplementary to an original lease: Asklepiades, a hundred aroura holder of the troops of Antiochos who had leased his holding to some farmers, agrees to share the crops on the basis that two-thirds go to him and one-third to the lessees</summary>
